name: The Masked Singer

next_episode_to_air.name: Group C Premiere: Who Are You Fest

overview: Celebrities compete in a singing competition with one major twist: each singer is shrouded from head to toe in an elaborate costume, complete with full face mask to conceal his or her identity. One singer will be eliminated each week, ultimately revealing his or her true identity.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: This season, the 18 fully disguised celebrity singers will be split into three groups of six: Group A, Group B and Group C. Group A will kick off the first three episodes as they are whittled down to three singers, taking off masks as they go. Then Group B will take the stage as they go from six to three, then Group C. The final nine masked contestants from all three groups will then come together as they continue to battle for the Golden Mask Trophy. Season Three will introduce all-new custom-made costumes for the celebrity singers to wear, including The Robot, The Frog, The Banana, The Mouse, Miss Monster and The Llama, among others.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: The Season Five contestants boast a combined 26 Grammy Award nominations, nine multi-Platinum singles, four Academy Award nominations, three Super Bowl appearances, six gold medals and two world records! All will be unmasked, but only one will win the coveted Golden Mask Trophy.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: The Season Six contestants boast a combined 85 Grammy Nominations and 27 wins, three Academy Award nominations, 12 Emmy Nominations, 12 Razzie Award Nominations, two Super Bowl appearances and two Lifetime Achievement Awards.

seasons.name: Season 8
seasons.overview: The formatting for the season sees three contestants battle in each episode, with one eliminated mid-show while the other two battle out. A king/queen is crowned at the end of each episode who then moves on to the following episode, while the other in the top two gets eliminated. The season also includes themed nights for the first time.

seasons.name: Season 10
seasons.overview: In honor of its milestone 10th season, "The Masked Singer" celebrates with the biggest and boldest costumes in the show's history -- with the buzziest and brightest celebrities underneath. The season features the return of special theme nights.

episodes.name: Season 5 Premiere: Return of the Masks
episodes.overview: THE MASKED SINGER returns in its game-changing fifth season, with all-new jaw-dropping costumes, surprise appearances and unexpected twists that will upend the competition. In the season premiere, "Group A" performs as guest host Niecy Nash takes the stage.

episodes.name: Finale
episodes.overview: All three remaining singers will perform, all three will be unmasked, but only one singer will be awarded the Golden Mask Trophy in the Season Five finale.

episodes.name: Masks Back: The Good, The Bad & The Cuddly, Round 1
episodes.overview: TV's favorite guessing game returns with an all-new twist -- each new costume will be categorized in one of three groups: The Good, The Bad or The Cuddly. In Round One of Season Seven, characters from each category will duke it out to further themselves in the competition.

episodes.overview: The remaining four singers from "Group A" return to the stage for their second performances of the season. One will be unmasked and three will move on to the "Group A" finals.

episodes.overview: "Group A" returns for one final time when the three finalists perform. Two will be unmasked and only one will move on to the finale.

episodes.overview: A brand-new group of contestants take the stage for the first time, each representing Team Good, Team Bad, or Team Cuddly! These new singers kick off Round One of the battle to keep their masks on and make it to the season finale.

episodes.overview: Round Two continues, as the remaining four singers in this group return to battle for their second performances.

episodes.name: The Mask of Least Resistance, Round 3
episodes.overview: Round Three continues, as the four remaining singers duke it out for Team Good, Team Bad and Team Cuddly. One singer will be unmasked and the final three move on to the Round Three finals.

episodes.name: One Mask Hurrah, Round 3 Finals
episodes.overview: In the third and final round of the competition, the final three singers perform for the last remaining coveted spot this season. Two singers will be unmasked and the final singer will move on to the Season Seven finale.

episodes.name: Road to the Finals
episodes.overview: Before a winner is crowned, take a journey through Season Seven with all of The Good, The Bad and The Cuddly characters. Relive some of the most talked-about moments, watch the best performances and don't miss never-seen-before clues.

episodes.name: Season Finale
episodes.overview: Who will take the golden mask trophy? The winner from each of the three rounds will compete head-to-head in the Season Seven finale. Only one will take home the trophy: will it be a singer from Team Good, Team Bad or Team Cuddly?

8.name: Season 8
8.overview: The formatting for the season sees three contestants battle in each episode, with one eliminated mid-show while the other two battle out. A king/queen is crowned at the end of each episode who then moves on to the following episode, while the other in the top two gets eliminated. The season also includes themed nights for the first time.

episodes.name: Opening Night
episodes.overview: TV's favorite guessing game returns with all-new singers, all-new themed episodes and the "Champion of the Masked Singer" style competition. Every episode features sudden elimination and double unmaskings, but there is a new twist entering the competition this season: for the first time ever, panelists will have the opportunity to save a singer from looming elimination with the "Ding Dong Keep it On" Bell.

episodes.name: ABBA Night
episodes.overview: Mamma Mia - it's ABBA night on The Masked Singer! This week's episode is full of pop rock and disco nostalgia, as the reigning champ takes on two new celebrity singers, each performing iconic songs - including "Dancing Queen," "Fernando" and S.O.S." - from the one and only Swedish supergroup, ABBA.

episodes.name: New York Night
episodes.overview: The Masked Singer celebrates the Big Apple! This week's episode embraces both the glam and the grit of the city that never sleeps, as two new contestants take on the reigning champ from last week and sing a collection of songs synonymous with the history of New York.

episodes.name: DC Superheroes Night
episodes.overview: Three new singers enter the game on DC Superheroes night. While the audience and panelists celebrate their favorite iconic DC Superheroes in costume, celebrities vie for their chance at the champion of The Masked Singer in three brand-new costumes!

episodes.name: Sesame Street Night
episodes.overview: Elmo, Big Bird, Cookie Monster, Oscar the Grouch, The Count and Abby Cadabby bring the fun in a special Sesame Street episode.

episodes.name: Country Night
episodes.overview: Grab the cowboy boots and cowboy hats because The Masked Singer has gone country! Three celebrities will perform their favorite country songs, two will be unmasked, but only one singer will advance straight to the quarterfinals with California Roll.

episodes.name: '80s Night
episodes.overview: The Masked Singer goes retro with a trip back to the 80s! A brand-new group of singers belt out hit favorites from the neon decade, but only one will move forward in the competition as the other two unmask!

episodes.name: WB Movie Night
episodes.overview: Get your popcorn and settle in as The Masked Singer celebrates the cinema! The costumed celebrities perform iconic songs from hit Warner Bros. films from their 100 years of movie magic.

episodes.name: Masked Singer in Space
episodes.overview: Houston, we have a problem! The Masked Singer is even more out-of-this-world than usual in a special "outer space" themed episode.

episodes.name: Supreme Six
episodes.overview: In this special episode of The Masked Singer, the road to the finals is underway as we recap the journeys of the three remaining champions and the three remaining underdogs, while also looking back on the season and who has been eliminated thus far.

episodes.name: Battle Of The Saved
episodes.overview: The three "Saved by the Bell" singers - Mantis, Gargoyle and Medusa - compete for their spot in the quarter finals! All three were saved by the new "Ding Dong, Keep It On!" bell, but now two will be unmasked and only one will go on to be named the Group Champion.

episodes.name: Quarter Finals
episodes.overview: It's the Quarter Finals on The Masked Singer, and the British are coming! Watch the final four compete for a spot in the coveted Semi-Finals, performing hit songs from artists across the pond. Only one will be unmasked!

episodes.name: Semi-Finals
episodes.overview: The remaining three celebrity singers perform, but only two move on to compete in the season finale.

episodes.name: Finale
episodes.overview: The final two contestants each perform two songs; one celebrity is crowned the Season 9 winner.

episodes.overview: Five celebrities perform songs from the 2000s and one is unmasked.

episodes.name: A Celebration of Elton John
episodes.overview: The singers celebrate the music of Sir Elton John. Robin Thicke opens the show with a performance of “Tiny Dancer.”

episodes.name: Harry Potter Night
episodes.overview: A special Harry Potter-themed episode; former contestant Adrienne Bailon-Houghton performs.

episodes.name: One Hit Wonders Night
episodes.overview: Who Let the Dogs Out? - it's one hit wonders night on The Masked Singer! The iconic competition series celebrates its milestone 10th season as the legacy continues with a special "One Hit Wonders Night" featuring four new celebrities singing a collection of songs that were once all the rage!

episodes.name: Trolls Night
episodes.overview: The Masked Singer cranks up the color with a night of nonstop pop, grooving to unforgettable boy band chart toppers to celebrate the release of Trolls Band Together, the newest chapter in the blockbuster musical franchise. The Trolls stars, Poppy and Branch, infiltrate the sound studio, delivering a glittery opening song and sneaking special clues to the panel.

episodes.name: Disco Night
episodes.overview: Can you dig it? It's time to boogie as The Masked Singer celebrates the Disco era, kicking off with a special performance by the legendary disco band The Trammps. Group A returns for their final competition and two will be unmasked - unless the panel uses the Ding Dong Keep It On Bell!

episodes.name: I Wanna Rock
episodes.overview: The Masked Singer is with the band! Tonight, the show celebrates Rock 'n' Roll as the Group B finalists rock out to legendary songs from bands like Kiss, Jon Bon Jovi and Mr. Big. The Masked Singer's very own Banana from Season 3 and legendary Poison front man, Bret Michaels, gives a special performance. Two celebrities will be unmasked leaving only one to move on to the season finale.

episodes.name: Holiday Sing-Along
episodes.overview: Holiday splendor and masked merriment collide in this beloved yuletide special featuring all-new jaw-dropping surprise performances from Season 10 contestants, spectacular sing-along fun from Masked Singer alumni and The Masked Singer carolers.

episodes.name: Soundtrack to My Life
episodes.overview: It's the Group C Finals on The Masked Singer and tonight, the finalists perform songs representing key moment in their life, such as "Georgia on my Mind," "I'm Going Down," and "Johnny B Goode." Two celebrities will be unmasked leaving only one to move on to the season finale.

episodes.name: Season 10 Finale
episodes.overview: The final four contestants perform all-new songs before the audience and panel cast their votes. The bottom two singers unmask, and then the final two go head-to-head one last time. Only one will take home the Golden Mask trophy and be crowned the Season Ten Winner!

10.name: Season 10
10.overview: In honor of its milestone 10th season, "The Masked Singer" celebrates with the biggest and boldest costumes in the show's history -- with the buzziest and brightest celebrities underneath. The season features the return of special theme nights.

episodes.name: Season 11 Premiere: Rita We Love Your Ora
episodes.overview: The season premiere kicks off with an exciting performance by new panelist Rita Ora, special celebrity performances and a jaw-dropping reveal no one sees coming.

episodes.name: Group B Premiere: The Wizard of Oz Night
episodes.overview: Join us for a trip down the Yellow Brick Road on the "The Wizard of Oz" night on The Masked Singer. Four new celebrities sing their hearts out and celebrate iconic moments from the legendary "The Wizard of Oz" film. The Masked Singer's very own Sun, LeAnn Rimes, returns to the stage to sing her rendition of "Somewhere Over The Rainbow."

episodes.name: Group C Premiere: Billy Joel Night
episodes.overview: Come "Just The Way You Are" to celebrate "Billy Joel Night" on The Masked Singer! Panelist, Robin Thicke kicks off the episode with a rockstar rendition of "My Life." Then, the last group of celebrity singers belt out classic tunes from the iconic "Piano Man" himself, Bill Joel!

episodes.name: TV Theme Night
episodes.overview: On The Masked Singer's "TV Theme Night," it's time to celebrate the very best of the small screen! Panelists Ken Jeong, Robin Thicke, Jenny McCarthy Wahlberg, and Rita Ora open the show with a performance of one of television's most iconic theme songs from "Gilligan's Island". Then, Season Eleven contestants pay tribute to theme songs including "Scooby-Doo," "The Hills" and "Good Times".

episodes.name: Group C Finals: Shower Anthems Night
episodes.overview: On The Masked Singer's "Shower Anthems Night," it's time to belt out some squeaky-clean tunes! The Season Eleven Contestants start the night with a showstopping group performance, and then serenade the audience with iconic songs that are best sung at full volume in the shower!

episodes.name: Transformers Night
episodes.overview: The Masked Singer's "Transformers Night," celebrates the 40th anniversary of Transformers! Special Guests Optimus Prime and Bumblebee appear throughout the episode to open the show, deliver clues - and even transform into backup dancers! Each celebrity singer will perform a song that was featured in a "Transformers" movie.

episodes.name: Group A Finals: Queen Night
episodes.overview: We Will Rock You on "Queen Night" of The Masked Singer! The group A contestants are put Under Pressure as they pay homage to iconic rock band, Queen! Two celebrities will break free of their masks and one will move on to the quarter finals!

episodes.name: Girl Group Night
episodes.overview: It's "Girl Group Night" on The Masked Singer! Panelists Ken Jeong, Robin Thicke, Jenny McCarthy Wahlberg, and Rita Ora open the show with a group performance of Spice Girls anthem, "Wannabe." Then, Girl Group veterans and The Masked Singer's very own member of the "Lambs" trio, Carnie Wilson, and "Black Widow", Raven Symone, return to The Masked Singer stage before the Season Eleven contestants rock out to Girl Group classics like "Free Your Mind," "I'm So Excited," and "Wide Open Spaces."

episodes.name: Group B Finals:  Soundtrack of My Life
episodes.overview: It's "Soundtrack Of My Life" night on The Masked Singer! The Group B Finalists open the evening with a showstopping performance of "It's My Life" by Bon Jovi. Throughout the episode, contestants perform songs that hold a special place in their hearts like "One Moment In Time," "It's Tricky," and "Carry On Wayward Son." The Season Eleven contestants boast a combined 22 Grammy Nominations, 11 Platinum Albums, 33 Teen Choice Nominations, 108 million Records Sold, 326 Film Appearances and have 1.7 billion Spotify Streams! Two celebrities are unmasked leaving one to move on to the quarter finals.

episodes.name: Quarter Finals: Final Four
episodes.overview: It's "Final Four" night on The Masked Singer! In the Quarter Finals, the final four contestants open the show with panelist Rita Ora's hit song, "Praising You!" Throughout the episode, contestants sing their hearts out to songs like "Price Tag," "I'm Yours," "Get On Your Feet," and "Unforgettable."

episodes.name: Road to the Semi-Finals
episodes.overview: In this special episode of The Masked Singer, take a walk down memory lane to relive the season's most exciting highlights as well as special performances from the final three. Then, see exclusive behind-the-scenes moments from the Season Eleven contestants.

episodes.name: Semi Finals: Then There Were Three
episodes.overview: The three remaining contestants battle it out for the final two spots as they serenade the audience with songs like "You Oughta Know," "Dancing In The Street," and "I Lived."

episodes.name: Finale: One Mask Takes It All
episodes.overview: It is time for the highly anticipated Season Eleven finale of The Masked Singer where "One Mask Takes It All!" Season Eleven culminates in the final two celebrities delivering exceptional performances of songs like, "Latch," "Heart of Glass," "Renegade," and "Don't Let The Sun Go Down On Me" before the winner is revealed!

episodes.name: Who Can It Be Now?
episodes.overview: Celebrity performances from five all-new masked celebrities and a jaw-dropping reveal.

episodes.name: Footloose Night
episodes.overview: Celebrating the 40th anniversary of the iconic film "Footloose."
